Cape Town – A 22-year-old man appeared in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court yesterday over an alleged gang-related stabbing, Western Cape police spokesperson Siyabulela Malo said on Tuesday. The stabbing took place at about 11.45pm last Wednesday on the second floor of the Wynberg Magistrate's Court. The victim, Chad Jansen, of the Americans gang, bled to death at the court. According to a police source, the Daily Voice reported, chaos had ensued inside the court building as the Americans gang from Parkwood and Six Bobs from Lotus River took out knives and started fighting. Jansen had gone to Wynberg with a gang member who was appearing in court. On a video which surfaced on social media, Jansen can be seen lying on a courtroom bench while a woman applies to pressure to his wounds and a man prays over him. Grassy Park police station commander, Colonel Dawood Laing told the Daily Voice: “The 22-year-old man was found at a known Six Bobs residence in New Horizons shortly after 7pm on Sunday. “He is a Zimbabwean Six Bob and was identified through the footage. He was charged with murder and will appear in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court. “In this case, the video footage is crucial, but witnesses also came forward and gave statements against him." 